        <updateDate>2007-02-06T19:23:16Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Satellite Consumer Protection Act of 2006 - Grants a satellite carrier under an injunction for certain secondary transmission violations a statutory license to provide distant network stations in specified local markets under prescribed conditions. Requires a satellite carrier as a condition of license use to deposit escrow funds with the Copyright Office. Imposes monetary penalties for license violations.</p> <p>Terminates such license authority after February 17, 2009.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
